Two things:
1. System properties file should be at root level of the project. 
Refer: https://github.com/heroku/java-getting-started


2. If that does not work for you you can instead use maven deployment

In your pom.xml
goto &lt;plugins&gt; section add following

```
      &lt;plugin&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;com.heroku.sdk&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;heroku-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;3.0.3&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;configuration&gt;
           &lt;jdkVersion&gt;17&lt;/jdkVersion&gt;
        &lt;/configuration&gt;
      &lt;/plugin&gt;
```

if you do not want to use procfile as well you can add config for that as well in configuration section.

```xml
&lt;configuration&gt;
  ...
  &lt;processTypes&gt;
     &lt;web&gt;java $JAVA_OPTS -cp target/classes:target/dependency/* Main&lt;/web&gt;
  &lt;/processTypes&gt;
&lt;/configuration&gt;
```

also you will see configuration for java opts there if required
Ref:
https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/deploying-java-applications-with-the-heroku-maven-plugin

If you want to understand or customize and use any other java version
you can have a look at :
https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/java-support#specifying-a-java-version

